                I usually work from coffee shops or anywhere where WiFi is reliable. 
                <br/>
                Check out <a target="_blank" href="https://workfrom.co/awesome/42066/scouted">places I've scouted for remote work!</a>
            </div>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Role:</strong> Web Developer - Digital Nomad</li>
                <li><strong>Born:</strong> Fairfax, Virginia.</li>
                <li><strong>Languajes:</strong> English and Spanish</li>
                <li><strong>Interests:</strong> Coffee Shops, bubble tea, cryptocurrency, websites, cats.</li>
            </ul>



        </div>
    </div>
  <br />
    <hr />

    <p>


        This site is built with &lt;3 using <a target="_blank" href="http://purecss.io/">pure v0.5.0</a> based on the Responsive Side Menu layout.


    </p>

    <hr />
</div>
<script>

    $(function () {



        function random_imglink() {

            var myimages = new Array()

            //specify random images below. You can have as many as you wish

            myimages[0] = "img/about/tho.jpg"

            myimages[1] = "img/about/tho2.jpg"

            myimages[2] = "img/about/tho3.jpg"

            myimages[3] = "img/about/tho4.jpg"
            myimages[4] = "img/about/tho5.jpg"
            myimages[5] = "img/about/tho6.jpg"
            myimages[6] = "img/about/tho7.jpg"



            var ry = Math.floor(Math.random() * myimages.length)

            $('#aboutMePic').html('<img class="aboutPic" src="' + myimages[ry] + '" title="Thomas Rosales" />');



        }

        random_imglink();

        $('img').on('dragstart', function (event) { event.preventDefault(); });

    });



</script>
